  <https://w3id.org/financialDT> rdfs:seeAlso "https://spec.edmcouncil.org/fibo/";
    owl:versionIRI <https://w3id.org/financialDT>;
    owl:imports <http://www.w3.org/2006/time#>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/creator> "Nizar Al-Ahmad, Anelia Kurteva, Yuting Zhang";
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> """Financial Digital Twin Ontology (financialDT) is a proof-of-concept ontology developed to investigate the use of semantic technologies in modelling financial operational risk through multi-modal data integration. The ontology provides a formal conceptual framework for constructing knowledge graphs capable of representing financial institutional structures, product lifecycles, and risk dynamics in a unified semantic model.

The ontology adopts a layered modular architecture comprising three principal layers: the Financial Institutional Layer (FIL), the Risk Layer, and the Financial Product Layer.

The Financial Institutional Layer is conceptually aligned with principles from FIBO and models the core organisational, contractual, and account-level semantics required to represent financial institutions and their operational structure.

The Risk Layer is inspired by ISO 31000 and provides a structured representation of risk sources, risk events, exposures, assessments, mitigation strategies, and control actions. It enables explicit modelling of risk identification, analysis, evaluation, and treatment within a financial digital twin context.

The Financial Product Layer captures the semantics necessary to represent financial products and their lifecycle states. Mortgages are used as a proof-of-concept instantiation to demonstrate how product structures interact with institutional entities and risk mechanisms.

The layered modular structure allows individual components of the ontology to be reused independently or integrated selectively, supporting interoperability with institution-specific organisational models and product definitions while preserving a coherent global risk reasoning framework.""";
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/license> """This ontology is released under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0) licence.

It conceptually aligns with and reuses ideas from the Financial Industry Business Ontology (FIBO) without importing it.
Users who reuse FIBO-aligned concepts or mappings from this ontology remain responsible for complying with the
original FIBO licensing terms as published by the EDM Council and the Object Management Group (OMG).""" .
  
